claim.claim-text:
35. A method of extending the life of a radiant heating lamp used within a semiconductor processing apparatus, the method including: 
running current through a filament within the lamp, said filament having a capacity of at least 3 kW, thereby causing the filament to heat and expand; 
as the filament heats and expands, allowing a central section comprising at least 70% of the filament, as measured lengthwise, to expand laterally; 
ceasing current flow through the filament, thereby causing it to cool; and 
allowing the filament to cool and contract.

41. The method of claim 35 further including: 
as the filament heats, allowing the expansion of the filament to be absorbed by the compression of one or more buffer zones, proximately placed at either one or both ends of the filament; 
as the filament cools, allowing the buffer zones to re-compress the central section of the filament, such that it is returned to about its original size and position.
